    public interface Struct

    • Method Detail

      • getAlignment

        int getAlignment()
        Returns the value of the 'Alignment' attribute. The default value is "0". The internal alignment of array fields in byte. 0 means all elements are directly after each other. Values above 0 mean that fields smaller than the value will be stuffed with padding bytes until the alignment matches.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Alignment' attribute.
        See Also:
        setAlignment(int), CommonPackage.getStruct_Alignment()

      • getFields

        org.eclipse.emf.common.util.EList<DataTypeA> getFields()
        Returns the value of the 'Fields' reference list. The list contents are of type DataTypeA. The data types of which the structure is composed of in sequential order.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Fields' reference list.
        See Also:
        CommonPackage.getStruct_Fields()
